
Cisco switches have a feature called auto-mdix that notices when the wrong cable is used and automatically changes its logic to make the link work.


-- How to Use Straight-Through & Crossover Cables --

Similar devices require crossover cables
· Switch to Switch connections require crossover cables
· Router to Router connections require crossover cables

Dissimilar devices require  straight-thru cables
· Switch to Router connections require straight-thru cables



-- Ethernet Straight-Through Cable --

Transmit on Pins 1,2  --->  Receive on Pins 1,2    
Receive on Pins 3,6   <---  Transmit on Pins 3,6

1,2 on Left <---> 1,2 on Right
3,6 on Left <---> 1,2 on Right 


-- Ethernet Crossover Cable --

Transmit on Pins 3,6  --->  Receive on Pins 1,2    
Receive on Pins 3,6   <---  Transmit on Pins 3,6

3,6 on Left <---> 1,2 on Right
1,2 on Left <---> 3,6 on Right 
